From: Charlie Jenkins <charlie@rivosinc.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jan 2025 18:36:23 -0800
Subject: perf tools x86: Use generic syscall scripts
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: a874d1f6f107685af28ddca01dbe26846935d960
Patch-mainline: v6.14-rc1
References: perf-sle16.1-v6.19-userspace-update

Use the generic scripts to generate headers from the syscall table for
both 32- and 64-bit x86.

Signed-off-by: Charlie Jenkins <charlie@rivosinc.com>
Tested-by: Arnaldo Carvalho de Melo <acme@redhat.com>
